    "body": "> Hi Helder, The issue arises because your genesis file includes a rule for validating blocks - that they must have a blocktime of minimum 4 seconds, but the chain you are importing has blocks with only 3 seconds between them.\r\n> You can't increase blocktime, since this renders previous blocks invalid. Let us know if this is unclear to you from the documentation or if you expect a different result! If not, I'll go ahead and close this ticket.\r\n\r\n@vmichalik I know that i can't change the genesis but how i fix this issue?\r\nAnd i notice the old client don't have this rules for header validation. \r\n(old client)\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12281088/133992469-29f8d71c-2110-4d9b-bc22-996b31da14f2.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nSo my genesis file is the same as other older blocks nothing change only my upgrade of besu from 1.40 to 21.1.3. With the older version i can import the blockchain but with the new i can't. \r\n\r\nWhy is the reason for create one block in less than 3 seconds and other validators accepted?? exist any issue with difference in timestamps ?\r\n\r\nAnd how i resolve this problem?",
