    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "hey @helderjnpinto,\r\n\r\nWe have worked out what the underlying issues were. Blocks can on occasion be created too early due to the timer returning too early in some cases. This is largely mitigated in the latest version of Besu by how we determine the block header timestamp.\r\n\r\nThere is also a bug in the version of Besu you are using which causes the IBFT2 header validation for the block period to not validate the block timestamp correctly which is why those blocks are being allowed to be added to the chain. This bug is not present in the latest version of Besu.\r\n\r\nThe solution to fix this and allow for upgrading to the new version with an IBFT2 chain that has incorrect block header timestamps is to\r\n- Decrease the existing block period in the IBFT2 config to a lower value that satisfies the block header validation. In your case that would be to reduce the block period to 3s.\r\n- Allow for changing the block period using a transition #2797 so the original block period can be used for new blocks.\r\n\r\nOnce #2797 is complete it will be possible for you to upgrade your IBFT2 chain to the latest version of Besu.\r\n",
